race.comment: GIN TWIST (9) is a filly by boom sire Home Affairs who kicks off for the Hayes yard. Her latest jump out at Flemington was excellent to the eye, showing speed and gapping her rivals. She looks ready to go for one of the best 2yo stables in the country. LA GITANA (10) is a Home Affairs filly on debut for the Hayes yard who won a recent jumpout at Pakenham in good fashion. She looks ready to go and will take beating. ETERNAL JOY (8) debuted in a small field at Geelong and ran well for second as a $3 chance. That experience should hold her in good stead. BRAZEN DECHAMBEAU (2) was okay in G3 company on debut and kicks off here with a spell under his belt. Can improve this time in. OUR BRAVE BOY (5) is a Brave Smash gelding on debut for the Stokes yard who has jumped out well and can figure.
